comments.body:
Hmm, I see where the confusion comes from - `SetFuzzedErrNo()` does not _return_ the value but rather sets the global variable `errno` to it.

What about this:

```suggestion
    // Have a permanent error at bind_errnos[0] because when the fuzzed data is exhausted
    // SetFuzzedErrNo() will always set the global errno to bind_errnos[0]. We want to avoid Bind()
    // returning -1 and setting errno to EAGAIN repeatedly because a legit code should retry on
    // temporary errors leading to an infinite loop.
```

